Ansible install with python and pip3
https://github.com/g0t4/course2-ansible-gs/tree/master/install

Installtion for other distro
https://docs.ansible.com/ansible/latest/installation_guide/installation_distros.html#requirements-for-adding-new-distributions
###########################
sudo dnf install python3.11 -y
sudo dnf install python3.11-pip -y
python3.11 -m pip install ansible
############################

Autocomplication ansible commands 
#############################
python3.11 -m pip install argcomplete
activate-global-python-argcomplete
source /home/ec2-user/.zshenv
source  /home/ec2-user/.bash_completion
##############################
Autocomplication ansible commands for ubuntu
sudo apt-get install python3-argcomplete
sudo activate-global-python-argcomplete
##############################


Configure SSH with Traget node 
https://jay75chauhan.medium.com/install-ansible-on-ubuntu-and-configure-a-control-node-and-a-target-node-d40ab145c153

Configuration ansible.cfg 

To check what config has beed changed  in ansible.cfg
############
ansible-config dump --only-changed

To check config list 
############
ansible-config list

For default inventory to be used on the command
###########
[defaults]
inventory=/home/ec2-user/inventroty

Use --diff mode to check what will be change on the Managed host(Client servers) It shows what going to be change
##########
[diff]
always = true

##########
Use --check mode will use to check the changed status for all the managed hosts.


To check the inventory list which is in /etc/ensible/hosts i.e all managed host with group and individual. 
############
ansible-inventory --list --yaml

To check the default ansible collection and modules, if we remove ansible, we can still get  it from ansible core as 
with ansible.builtin.ping
Installing manaully get the precedence 
If the collection is installed by python, it "won't" remove the collection instaed it will remove by manaully installe collection.
###########################
ansible-galaxy collection list <collection>
ansible-doc --list
ansible-doc -t inventory <collection>
ansible-galaxy collection install <comumnity.general:5.5.0>


Fully qualified
###############
ansible.builtin.ping           module/connection pluging/etc
namespace collection content   content type
